REVIEW_TEXT: As of now it works fine, but outdoor unit makes noise except that everything is fine. Cooling is good as well.  Some people might know that remote has LED screen with backlit feature, in order to activate backlit, press and hold any button for 3 seconds, and it automatically turns off within 10 seconds. Installation was not up to the mark. Flipkart mentioned Rs: 1599 /- for standard installation, however installation guy took Rs: 1800 /-. Even they didn't need to drill the wall, because they took pipes out from the ventilator and outdoor unit installed on sun-shade. Installation people were unprofessional. I am happy about cooling, but I have to check it in Summer ( After April ). I didn't check power bills yet. I hope it helps someone to choose right product as per they needs.

REVIEW_TEXT: A Champion ACThis is the 4th AC in my home the other 3 are Voltas(6yr old), Midea (1yr Old), Samsung (2 year old). Pricing - I got the 1 ton 3star inverter at 23800 after all the offers. Quite reasonable compare to other brands. I was about to order Midea only as I am satisfied with that but some review was not good so ordered this. 4 out of 5. Delivery - Delivered in 3-4 days and installed after 2 days. 4 Out of 5. Product - well build inner and outer unit. It has Vertical and Horizontal swing which is not there in any of my other ACs. 5 out of 5. Cooling - Just tested for half hour not much. Seems good so far. I will update this in summer again. Installation - OMG. Best Installation experience so far. Got 3-4 calls from Onida Team too pre and post installation. Installation guys were nice people too and talking politely and one of the best installation of any product so far. 5 out of 5. I do spend lots and lots of time before ordering anything so feel free to order Onida. I am happy with my Midea AC too. Good cooling and awesome energy efficiency. Thank you.

REVIEW_TEXT: As of now it works fine, but outdoor unit makes noise except that everything is fine. Cooling is good as well.  Some people might know that remote has LED screen with backlit feature, in order to activate backlit, press and hold any button for 3 seconds, and it automatically turns off within 10 seconds. Installation was not up to the mark. Flipkart mentioned Rs: 1599 /- for standard installation, however installation guy took Rs: 1800 /-. Even they didn't need to drill the wall, because they took pipes out from the ventilator and outdoor unit installed on sun-shade. Installation people were unprofessional. I am happy about cooling, but I have to check it in Summer ( After April ). I didn't check power bills yet. I hope it helps someone to choose right product as per they needs.

REVIEW_TEXT: A Champion ACThis is the 4th AC in my home the other 3 are Voltas(6yr old), Midea (1yr Old), Samsung (2 year old). Pricing - I got the 1 ton 3star inverter at 23800 after all the offers. Quite reasonable compare to other brands. I was about to order Midea only as I am satisfied with that but some review was not good so ordered this. 4 out of 5. Delivery - Delivered in 3-4 days and installed after 2 days. 4 Out of 5. Product - well build inner and outer unit. It has Vertical and Horizontal swing which is not there in any of my other ACs. 5 out of 5. Cooling - Just tested for half hour not much. Seems good so far. I will update this in summer again. Installation - OMG. Best Installation experience so far. Got 3-4 calls from Onida Team too pre and post installation. Installation guys were nice people too and talking politely and one of the best installation of any product so far. 5 out of 5. I do spend lots and lots of time before ordering anything so feel free to order Onida. I am happy with my Midea AC too. Good cooling and awesome energy efficiency. Thank you.

REVIEW_TEXT: Bought the AC for 29k. Was very sceptical about the performance, brand value and quality. But to my surprise the quality is at par , thanks to panasonic build quality is great and value for money is beyond expectations. So let me summarise in pros and cons.Pros1. Timely delivery and installation with seasoned technicians.2. Budget friendly with Japanese quality.3. Ergonomically design indoor as well as outdoor units.4. Electricity consumption is very very low and has the dual inverter technology as mentioned ( Hope so ). 5. In over night use of 8 to 10 hours only 2 units consumed @ 28 degree and it cools sufficiently at this temp no need to go to 24 or less.Cons1. Some cracking sounds were noticed but as per manual these sounds are due to expansion and contraction of plastic as well as metal parts due to temp difference nothing more than that.2. In door unit is noisy as compared with other AC. And blower motor makes humming sound while in operation at low speeds.

REVIEW_TEXT: The only issue with this laptop - WLAN card does not works with 5Ghz Wifi, when relayed on certain channel. e.g. in my case 5GHz channel is 149 and connection to 5Ghz fails. Surprisingly I have 2 other old lenovo models and they are able to connect flawlessly. And also if the channel is changed to 40 the WLAN connects to 5GHz. I have checked that laptop can connect to my friend's Wifi if on lower channels. So clearly compatibility issue which is not nice when you are spending this much of amount. I have called customer care and they are going to replace the WLAN Card.Otherwise very fast and lightining speed.

REVIEW_TEXT: Speaking of cost the Lenovo thinkpad is a great deal but performance out of the box you get is very laggy and definitely you should go for upgrading the RAM to 8GB (and even SSD too if you got money in your pocket). Speaking of upgrading the RAM only, is a must to do step if you are planning to use your laptop seamlessly on your day today task. But the upgrade is worth to do because if you buy a laptop for about 35k (which will cost you the same with upgrade of RAM in this laptop) you get a premium experience in this laptop than any other.The premium experience you get from this laptop is from the display, speaker, keyboard and mouse setup. REVIEW_TEXT: iphone 11 is a very good phone to buy only if you can compromise for the display. The display on this is device is pretty good but you can get other options with better displays in this price segment.If you can survive with an HD+ LCD panel with thicker bezels and a notch up top then this is a very good phone for you.Cameras are awesome, battery backup excellent, great performance and a decent premium look. PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: Previously I was using one plus 3t it was a great phone And then I decided to upgrade I am stuck between Samsung s10 plus or iPhone 11 I have seen the specs and everything were good except the display it's somewhere between 720-1080 and it's not even an amoled it's an LCD display But I decided to go with iPhone because I have never used an IOS device I have Been an android user from the past 9 years I ordered IPhone 11 (128gb) product redMy experience after using 3 weeks 1. The delivery was on time and I came in good packaging 2. First impression were awesome the display is not as bad as it is written in the spec list it's the high quality LCD Panel that you will get in any phone and using dark made/light mode will not make any difference since it's an LCD panel 3. Cameras were excellent even in the night 5? I have also uploaded some sample images 4. Performance mind blowing Apple A13 chip is super fast everything is buttery smooth 5. Battery 3110 mah and the optimisation of Apple and IOS 13 you will get good battery life and you will not get fast charger out of box you have to buy this separately The final thing I wanna say is if you are on a budget of 60-70 go for the iPhone 11 and If you have enough money go for the iPhone 11 Pro Max don't buy the iPhone 11 Pro (My opinion)Or you can get iPhone 11 and Apple Watch series 5 with same price of 11 pro The phone is great you will not regret after buying it go for it ??
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: It's a must buy who is looking for an upgrade from previous generation of iPhones. If you are using XR then still you can hold on for sometime and upgrade to 2020 model else this phone is a must buy . Camera quality is amazing and wide angle is something to count upon. Performance wise it's amazing and feels premium while holding in hand. So a big YES for this device. Go for 128 GB variant as the 4K videos will occupy lots of space and the storage can get over very quickly. Try to buy it within some offer to get the best value for money.
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: *Review after 10 months of usage*Doesn't seem bulky with decent touch and camera. The "standard maintained" quality of IPhone. Go for it, if your budget is not more enough for pro models. It's a value for money among the 11 series Stereo speakers are so good, you will love the stereo sound. Battery backup is not decent but still better than Iphone 7 and 8.Processor is fast, the phone doesn't lag at all even with heavy games, waterproof, faster face id and with no fingerprint scanners. The camera modes especially the Portrait modes "studio light" and "stage light", are way too good. So natural pics not filtered ones which you get with OnePlus phones. Go for it, you won't be disappointed
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: Value for moneyIts awesome mobile phone in the world ...Display was very good and bright ..Trust me freinds you r never regret after Buying..Just go for it....I love this phone and i switch to iphone x to 11
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: Best budget Iphone till date  go for it guys without second thought. Let me explain you guys about Camera, Display, battery, and performance. Camera: at this price range there is no comparison of camera, you'll love the picture quality as well as video quality. I am a Vlogger I wanted an iPhone with 4k video by front camera and I got this phone and I am more than happy  Battery: I use this phone roughly as I am active social media person and I have a youtube channel. so the battery backup of this phone is far far better than Iphone x and I charge this phone once in a day despite of using this roughly.   Display: don't go on negative reviews about display. Earlier, I was using Iphone X since 1 n half years. I didn't see any major difference in display. The display quality is superb as it's Apple device. You can compare one plus amoled display with Iphone 11 display you'll get to know that Iphone 11 display is much better. Performance: the performance of this phone as same as Iphone 11 pro, there is 3 difference between Iphone 11 pro and Iphone 11. First is display, second you'll get ultra wide angle camera in iphone 11 pro, and third is display Resolution. Except these things there is no difference and performance remains the same. When you'll hold this phone you'll feel that you are holding a premium device  Like if my review helps.
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: It's been almost a month since I have been using this phone. I upgraded from an iPhone 8. The main issue with my 8 was battery and this phone is just awesome when it comes to battery. It lasts a day and a half for me with my regular use , internet connected always with 4g Can't move forward without saying this. Battery of this phone is a life saver when I am traveling or at work when I don't get the option to charge Camera is superb. Front cam selfies and back cam photos are just awesome. Since i came from the smaller phone category which was an iPhone 8 , I found it difficult to adjust first with the size of this phone, but after the days of usage, I got very much used to it. Watching a video or reading online is awesome with this bigger screen. I am very much happy with this upgrade I am adding few photos I have clicked. Night photography is awesome The pic in which the guy is stading was clicked at midnight 1.
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 (Black, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: It looks premium and sturdy. I have doubts on whether which one to go, either 11pro or 12 before. Reason why I picked up 11 pro:1. Premium feel with stainless steel at the sides and matte finish at the back whick you cannot expect in 12.2. Telephoto camera module. 3 camera layout adds more premium and pro feel which you cannot expect from 12.3. Battery optimization and capacity which is better in 11 pro.4. Power adapter which supports fast charging will be provided.5. Earpods will be included in the box.Reasons to pick 12:1. 5G support and Qualcomm Snapdragon Modem which is much better than 11pro intel modem however you can rethink as 5G facilities in India is a long way to go as even 4Gs are not working properly in our region.2. Boxy or squary feel of iphone 5 3. Magsafe charger which is not everyone's cup of tea as we rely on lightning charger.4. Improvement of ultra wide angle night mode.
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 Pro (Midnight Green, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: One of the better Iphones to come out in recent times. This is my third iPhone coming from iphone 4G to iPhone 6S and iPhone 11 Pro. Inbetween did use a dozen android phones including flagships like Note II, HTC M8, Nokia 8, LG V40 Thinq, Oppo Reno. Pros:Camera x 3 - Solid and very easy to get superb snaps in all types of lighting Front Cam - Excellent feature set including HighKey mono and Slowmo + TimelapseBattery - Solid 30 hours+ for above average usage much much better than older iphonesScreen - Easily the best screen i am coming from POLED screen of LG V40 and this looks so much rich with deep blacksChipset - A13 is the fastest chip and yes even faster than the 855+ SD that is newly launchedIOS - Optimized and slick + some new features. very fast Face Lock that works perfect even in low light condition Build - Solid yet handy - Good weight and BalanceCons:Price - could have been 10k lowerStorage options price - Local storage options are very pricey  Closed Ecosystem - Some may not like it
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 11 Pro (Midnight Green, 64 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: iPhone 6S Plus 64GB -> iPhone 12 128GBMy 2nd iPhone, upgraded after 5 years.Gorgeous display, stunning new blue colour, excellent camera, best hardware-software combination, that's how I would describe iPhone 12 as a package. Even though my previous iPhone had a 5.5 display and this one has 6.1 display, its overall body size is much smaller. Had to get used to it initially Opening/closing/loading of apps is fast. No issues there. Video playback on this screen looks gorgeous. Took the 128GB variant, just so that i don't have to backup to PC too often.Battery lasts a day, it drains a bit faster on weekdays when I use its Mobile hotspot for office work. No connectivity issues though.Few pics attached. Night shots look much better on iPhone 12.No charging brick in the box. But works with my old iPhones charger/cable. I still ordered 20W fast charging brick separately from Apple site though. And it does charge pretty fast.Flipkart delivery: Had done pre booking on the day they made it available on Flipkart. Awesome discount and old phone buy back offered. Had initial promised delivery date of 1st Nov, but got delivered on 4th Nov. Am not complaining though as I still got it prior to 6-9th Nov delivery that Apple's own website was showing for this blue coloured 128GB variant  Flipkart packaging uses no plastic
PRODUCT_TITLE: APPLE iPhone 12 (Blue, 128 GB)

REVIEW_TEXT: If you're in the market for a compact phone with probably the best cameras in a phone today, that does not sacrifice on performance or any of the flagship features then your decision must start and end with an iPhone. First of all Apple has created something that is a throwback to the best smartphones ever designed - the iphone 5 and 5S. While doing so Apple made sure that it did not compromise on power or performance. The 12 mini has all the features (ALL OF THEM!) of the bigger iPhone 12 - so basically its the same A14 processor, same cameras, same RAM, same OLED screen, same FaceID, same wireless charging, same water resistance, same 5G support and everything else! Except that this is a smaller sized phone physically, which is so comfortable to hold that you'll wonder what happened to the smartphone industry getting obsessed over making bigger devices every year.Fun fact : Literally 8 years ago in 2013 was when the iPhone 5S was announced. That was considered the gold standard in smartphone design. In 8 years we're carrying phones that are getting so uncomfortably big we have forgotten to use them with one hand. You know what's really funny? Human hands have stayed the same size in the last 8 years too. :DYou're not reading this for fun facts. You're really reading this review wondering if the battery life suffers because of the smaller battery on the mini compared to the regular sized iPhone 12. The simple answer - NOT REALLY!. Let me explain. Compared to the regular sized iPhone 12 - you will get ~1.5 hours less in terms of 100% - fully dead battery for the same level of usage on both phones. You can verify this via several YouTube channels that have tested this extensively. So basically for ~1.5 to 2 hours less battery life you get a phone that is so compact, without sacrificing anything else in terms of features. For me personally this means that I love my iPhone 12 mini. Convenience over 2 extra hours of battery life anyday for me. Plus I got a 20W fast charger that charges my mini from 10% - 100% in about ~45 minutes. My phone charges on Apple Carplay while I'm driving too. So 2 less hours of battery life is overrated for me. But you may disagree and that's fine.Final verdict : If ~1.5 to 2 hours of extra battery backup along with a slightly bigger screen means more for you and how you want to use your phone, buy the regular sized iPhone 12. But for 2 hours less battery backup you prefer the convenience of carrying around a smaller, lighter phone that has everything that the regular 12 has, then buy the 12 mini without a doubt! This is a question of your priorities. ALSO if you're wondering if suddenly typing on a smaller screen will become an issue coming from a bigger phone, you could not be more wrong! It took me all of only 3 hours to get used to typing on this screen. Just FYI - I switched to this from a OnePlus 7T so I'm really speaking the truth. :D We tend to underestimate the ability of our brain and fingers on how quickly we can adapt to change. :D

REVIEW_TEXT: Let's keep it simple,Phone is damn smooth and if you are coming from Android, you will really notice the difference no matter which smartphone you used earlier.Pros:1. Camera and image processing (portrait modes)2. Battery (7hrs screen on time) i.e. all day battery life3. iOS (If you are coming from Android, you will need 2 days to get used to it.. like gestures and all but once you are into it, there's no way turning back. Animations are refined and you will enjoy them)4. Face ID is super fast and 100% secure5. Performance is superior to most Android smartphone in market as of today in this price bracket. A12 it is !!6. Speakers are excellent7. Haptic feedback is next level. I can't explain in words.. in short it feels like someone is sitting inside and knocking phone's display Cons:1. Glass back costs half price of phone itself if in case you end up shattering it2. Phone is heavy.. 194 grams to be precise and when you add screen guard and back cover, it will add up and finally be around 210~230 grams3. Battery charging is slow. Like what else will you expect from a 5w charger.4. Front camera res is 7MP and will give you consistent results for 95% of time but for rest.. be prepared for some horrible selfies See, if you think that you are ok with a camera performance of 4/5, then blindly go with this phone. And if you are one who has camera as #1 priority then you must go for iPhone 11, it has better cameras.Pro Tip: Don't judge it's display and camera based on just on paper specs and numbers. Both are excellent and 99% people won't have any problem. One more thing.. if possible go with a 128 gigs variant. iPhones eat lot of space !!

Otherwise the performance of battery is very very nice3. Appearance -Light weight , easy to pick, slots (i.e. sim slot, charging port & buttons ) are in perfect place, & its slim look makes it perfect on the base of appearance. Only a thing which I dont like personally is there earphone slot which is in the bottom side cause I really prefer the upper side earphone slot.4. Performance -Smooth tackling, & boost speed makes you to play  higher capacity games without any problem, the 4GB RAM is enough to handle games like Pubg very smoothly. You can do lot of work at a time with no break. The performance will make joy to your heart.Overall it is good option for those who really want budget phone with all the latest updated functions & gestures, i will highly recommend this phone .

I never heard the brand.. just research and think when I was buying redmi 2, same thing came in my mind.. but in 2020 how it developed, same scenario I hope for Iqoo sub brand of Vivo India.DISPLAY::I like the design.. looks premiumSuper Amoled display with 180 hz touch response, but only 60hz refresh rate.Bit heavier while pick in hand but it is adjusted with time.Nice camera designSmall size front cam does not disturb too much while gaming or viewing movie as like in water drop notch.Heptic feedback while typing is amazing premium feel.SOUND:It does not have stereo speakers, but the speaker is very much loud and it does not feel absence of stereo.But while gaming it may cover the speaker. But I like it's loudness even you sound clarity even in high traffic or crowded place.Camera::48MP primary+ 13MP wide angle + 13MP telephoto with 20x zoom + 2 MP depth sensor sounds really great, but not up to the mark. May be the update make it awesome. If you are a camera addictive it's not so suit for you.Battery and Charging::A battery with 4440 mAh capacity and fast charging of 11Vx5A=55W . Makes it incredible. I have playing four games of PUBG in HDR with high refresh rate and playing few video songs on YouTube around 4hrs continuously it dropped from 100% to 74% only. And while charging from 17% to 100% tooks only 32 minutes. Really a jaw dropping experience.Processor::It's main feature on the top notch, Snapdragon 865 SoC with adreno 650 GPU, latest processor in 2020. Absolute fantastic, no lagging issue hang issue found so far. Best in Class, 8GB DDR5 RAM and 128 GB is enough for a normal user and copying is super fast with UFS 3.1. Beast in Class.Accessories::With it's package, one can obtain mobile handset with pre-applied protective film, which is better than the cheap temper glass which we can buy from store in 200-250 ruppees.One whitish transparent tpu back cover which is hard cover I like it's quality and it's premium feel.A wired earphone... Really ba wired headphone very good quality free with with it. Does not it awesome??Drawbacks:1) Camera quality is good but picture quality is very average, in outdoor it takes better picture but indoor pictures are not up to the mark. Need to improve. Coz a specs like 48+13+13+2 really hurts if not meet the expectations.2) heating issue, while playing PUBG or high graphics heavy games.. you feel the heat, even it has vapour chamber but not evaporated heat while playing games for long hours.3)Iqoo OS, is a developing OS. Lots of improvement is required, In such a premium phone, a OS like MIUI, EMUI or Oxygen OS like OS everyone of us expecting. But a funtouch like OS, Iqoo really pinching the real satisfaction.These are three major drawback, I have found so far while using my Iqoo 3 smartphone in these days. Hope a better update in future which may vanish these drawbacks.CONCLUSION: In conclusion part, I just want to say that if you are a game lover or using a phone for day to day works, just go for it hassle free, if you are a camera lover like to shoot best pictures, go for other phone like Honor P30 or Samsung S20 or MI10.But I am satisfied coz I like to play game basically in such phone and I got it under RS 35000.Thanks for your patience of reading my review and if you like my review, kindly tap a like. Thank you :)Best RegardsManas, Assam

REVIEW_TEXT: After using it for 1 month:Unbelievable battery life. It is 6000mAh but feels like 7000. It never asks for charging before 2 days. You will probably charge it twice a week if you are a normal user.It is an absolute winner in talktime too. Every other branded phone would switch off before this one. Display is crisp enough for day to day usage. Social apps, media, music, etc.Back side has a nice grip and a non slippery texture. You will use the case provided in the box anyway. Touch screen is butter smooth. I was not expecting much from the camera but it is surprisingly good. The stock camera is good enough if you know how to use it. I used Open Camera though. No unwanted apps pre installed on this phone. I charge it slowly to reduce battery deterioration. But the 20w charger provided is fast enough.Security patches come regularly. Phone never hangs or crashes. Antenna is powerful. You get full signals for WiFi or SIM. Loud speaker is, well, loud. Earpiece is loud too. I overheard a phone conversation completely from 2ft away. Get it for yourself, your family or your old folks. It is perfect. Not for people with weak hands. It weighs around 218g. Not easy to pickpocket either. Your pants would feel lighter instantly.

REVIEW_TEXT: I really miss the old Nokia devices with 4-5" screens. Nowadays almost all devices are 6.5"+. I really hate that. This one seems too big because i was a Nokia Lumia 630 user. Now talking about Nokia 5.4, the build quality is great.Display - Display is good, I've no problem with HD+ resolution, so it will be 8-10.Processor - SD 662 is faster than I expected, works effortlessly. 9-10Back Camera - 48mp is really good even in night mode, wide angle lens needs more light. If the light is less it will look really bad more like a 2mp camera. Macro camera is bad, or maybe it's just that I don't know how to use it. Overall 8.5-10Front camera - 16mp looks bad in low light, not tried in daylight. Overall 7-10Battery - It will last full day with normal usage. 7.5-10This is an Android one Device so no bloatware issue.In the beginning Camera app was freezing and Crashing but nokia fixed it with update.My only complain is this device is really Big, 6.4" display with bezels almost like a small tab. My Nokia Lumia 630 has perfect screen size, 4.5" display which fits quite well in the pocket. I hope nokia will make small devices soon. Edit - after 2 weeks of usage, the battery lasts 2 days easily. Very well optimisation, This was fixed after update.

REVIEW_TEXT: Overview: Great product with probably best specs at this price point. Decent camera, great looks, great battery and charging.Design:Looks great and classy due to gorilla glass at back. camera bump is slightly bigger but this issue can fixed by using cover. Phone is slightly bigger.Display:It has 6.67inch ips lcs display. Viewing angles are good has Decent brightness. There is screen bleeding around camera cutout and edges of display but not a big deal every lcd djisplay has screen bleeding and can be solved by using dark mode.Camera:Forget about megapixels it has Decent camera. back camera is good video quality is also good u can record video in 4k. macro camera is great.But front camera is not that great I don't know why it makes faces yellowish. hope it will be resolved in future updates.Battery and charging: Best in this price segment can be  used for  2 days in normal usage. It takes 1:20-25 min to full charge,above 58%in 30 min,85%in 1 hour. For me it's battery and charger was deal breaker.Performance:it has Snapdragon's 720g. Great performance. REVIEW_TEXT: Beast Unleashed!!!Update - Battery backup tested at 60Hz. Screenshots attached for fool proof evidence.Those of you who said that battery drains faster than other phones you might not be knowing that the phone by default runs at 120Hz refresh rate which no other phone in the indian market offers, it makes your screen smoother than any other phone at the budget segment but it has a price to pay, the battery drains out. I would say the phone at 60hz isn't as fast as 120hz but it's faster than any other 60hz device in the budget segment.For those of you who don't understand refresh rates of a display and want to get better battery backup out of your device that's so perfect in every other way but you think isn't that good when it comes to battery, you are fooling yourself i would say. Simply, GO TO SETTINGS > DISPLAY > REFRESH RATE > SELECT 60hz. Now, you'll see my screenshots prove right. This time I did everything a normal user does in 24 hours from moderate to heavy usage without using battery saver mode, think what you can get with the battery saver mode ON at 60hz? Guys, its a 4500mah battery, no kidding. Facebook, Whatsapp, video calls, YouTube, some camera shots, video recording a lil bit and the screenshots prove that my phone is running for 23 hrs nearly without a charge with almost 9 hours of screen on-time. Beast they said. Well said!

REVIEW_TEXT: I'll not pretend to be an expert and review things as per their utility to me.I don't play a single game on my phone, so don't need heavy GPU and clock numbers etc etc.I do use the phone as an average young adult, making frequent videocalls. This phone's battery is an ally for at least a day and a half. Charging as many have stated via the Dash charger may not be as quick as many rivals in the game, for a good 3 hours of charge... this phone will do you good for a day and a half of moderate usage.I LOVE my music. This phone has one of the best in class audio outputs from its headphone jack. I was delighted by the audio output, both of the speakers as well as the 3.5mm jack on a medium to expensive pair of headphones. I am sometimes absorbed by the happenings of things, therefore I love to take pictures. I personally felt it has 2 more cameras than I would like it to have... But I was proved wrong when I saw its performance in terms of Ultra Macro. and the 48mp. The AI filters tend to saturate the colours a bit too much so I keep it on "Natural" setting... As an amateur, wannabe photographer it has a neat little Manual mode that I enjoyed toying around with. Overall it does a PLEASANT job with pictures.

It's super fast, has an awesome pair of camera, punchy speaker, good looks, beautiful screen, perfect size and an amazing user experience. REVIEW_TEXT: Totally worth the price if:- you are a iOS fan- like compact phone- want to switch from android to iPhone- you like clicking some good photos (camera is unbeatable)- you multitask (normal phones get stuck between apps, this will keep you going without a hiatus (lag)- you like to listen to music (have 2 speakers, one on the front, and another below; when I watch a movie with 4d-5d music, it feels like Dolby atmos)There a lot a technical advantages too which I dont want to get into (you can visit youtube for technical features).
PRODUCT_TITLE: Apple iPhone SE (Black, 64 GB) (Includes EarPods, Power Adapter)

REVIEW_TEXT: Let's face it. The main reason you're even considering this is because you want a compact phone that doesn't compromise on power. Getting OS updates for another 4-5 years, with a decent camera, waterproofing and wireless charging is just an added advantage. There's a few things it could've done better: 1. Battery is barely adequate for a day of moderate usage.2. The bezels could have been reduced to have more screen to body ratio.3. Night mode for the camera was a software feature that the A13 could smoothly implement.4. Fast charging ....Among others.But you knew all this already. It's been covered by almost every possible tech reviewer, news agency and social media platform. If you're still here in the reviews, you're just looking for a reason to justify the decision you've already made.If you're taking the leap from an Android phone(or anything before an iPhone 8), and miss the portability that phones used to have, just go for it. You won't be disappointed. The learning curve of going back to a small screen is minimal. For all the hate apple gets, it does know build quality (both hardware and software). The SE is no different. It will last for at least 3 years with basic care. The phone will not slow down, it won't crash, it will still be as secure as it is today. If you can afford the iPhone 11 now, or have the patience to wait for the iPhone 12 - Do it! But if you want the nostalgia of simpler times, the performance of a flagship device, and are not averse to carrying a power brick/bank with you. This one is for you.
PRODUCT_TITLE: Apple iPhone SE (Black, 64 GB) (Includes EarPods, Power Adapter)

REVIEW_TEXT: I have owned this model since it was launched in India.My biggest concern has been battery life. I have been extremely disappointed with it as I wasn't able to make it last through the day. The system needs a month or more to understand my usage and optimise battery usage. I am always (and I mean all the time) on Bluetooth and WiFi as I work from home. I listen to music all the time. The phone last 6 hours on average. This is far better than the battery life I had at the beginning.I cannot talk about the camera much as I rarely use it. It's serviceable. The screen auto brightness setting is very aggressive sometimes. Dims the screen when it needs to be bright.The fingerprint scanner is better but becomes unresponsive sometimes. Face recognition is pathetic.Software is solid. I have Android 11 and things have gotten better. Would I recommend it to people? Absolutely not for 41k. It's a phone that should be sold for 35k. It becomes a compelling buy at that point.I would give this phone 3.5 stars out of 5. I have given it a liberal 4 stars here.
PRODUCT_TITLE: SAMSUNG Galaxy S20 FE (Cloud Navy, 128 GB)  (8 GB RAM)

REVIEW_TEXT: Lousy design. Lid does not close fully, leaving a significant gap. Flipkart won't refund but will only replace the product with the same model since there is no defect! When the lid does not close, it is a DESIGN DEFECT. Small insects and lizards can easily get through the gap and can create havoc. Tried explaining to both Samsung and Flipkart but of no use. Very very disappointed with both Samsung and Flipkart. With Covid still prevalent in the country, it is difficult to visit a showroom and see a demo so we trust online portals like Flipkart but this experience has taught me that one should never buy white goods or other stuff that should be seen in a demo before buying! Very dissatisfied customer.

REVIEW_TEXT: Lousy design. Lid does not close fully, leaving a significant gap. Flipkart won't refund but will only replace the product with the same model since there is no defect! When the lid does not close, it is a DESIGN DEFECT. Small insects and lizards can easily get through the gap and can create havoc. Tried explaining to both Samsung and Flipkart but of no use. Very very disappointed with both Samsung and Flipkart. With Covid still prevalent in the country, it is difficult to visit a showroom and see a demo so we trust online portals like Flipkart but this experience has taught me that one should never buy white goods or other stuff that should be seen in a demo before buying! Very dissatisfied customer.

REVIEW_TEXT: Hello everyone, i would like to share my experience of BOSCH fully automatic washing machine. I purchasee in the month of Mar-20, and with one week of purchase  we went to native and locked over there due to COVID for almost 3months. We returned  back to blore in the month of june and started using BOSCH washing machine. Initially  everything was working smmothly, after a month washing started sounding very badly and we raised complain on sound. Then service men visited and checked and found that motor is damaged,need to be replaced. He called BOSCH customer service and requested  for replacement of new motor. But since motor is damages within a very short time and moreover we dont use much as i and wife stay at home, i requested for replacement of new machine. Unfortunately non of the BOSCH executives are responding us for replacement of either motor or machine. Such a irresponsible  behaviour.  Hence i request you all not to puchase BOSCH washing machine even though cost is less. All executives of BOSCH are good for nothing and completely  irresponsible...i am very much dissapponted on BOSCH  and i wont recomend to any one... Worst product...
